article.headline: Dayton 64, Northwestern St. 55
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Mark Jones scored a season-high 17 points to lead Dayton to a 64-55 victory over Northwestern State on Monday as the Demons wrapped up an unsuccessful trip to southwest Ohio. No. 22 Cincinnati beat Northwestern State 81-65 on Saturday. Monty Scott added 11 points for Dayton (5-3), all in the first half, and Warren Williams had 10. Jermaine Wallace, with 13 points, was the only player in double figures for Northwestern State (5-6). Jones scored the go-ahead 3-pointer for the Flyers with 6:28 to play and the score tied at 48. A jumper by Jones made it 60-55 with 1:42 remaining, and Williams accounted for the only points the rest of the way, making 4 of 4 free throws.
